Excellent! Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the components. Let me create a detailed analysis document.

## Complete Grid & SearchDropdown Component Analysis

### 1. GRID COMPONENT (`src/components/grid/grid.tsx`)

**Purpose**: A flexible grid layout component with keyboard navigation, supporting multi-column grids for displaying items like colors.

**Props Interface**:
```typescript
interface GridProps {
  children: ReactNode;
  itemCount: number;
  columns?: 3 | 4 | 5 | 6;  // Default: 4
  onActiveIndexChange?: (index: number) => void;
  onAction?: (index: number) => void;
}
```

**Key Features**:
- **State Management**: Uses `activeIndex` state to track selected item
- **Context Provider**: Provides `GridContext` with `activeIndex`, `setActiveIndex`, and `columns` to child GridItems
- **Dynamic Column Layout**: Uses CSS custom property `--grid-columns` set via inline style
- **Keyboard Navigation**:
  - Arrow Keys: Navigate left/right/up/down within grid
  - Enter: Triggers `onAction` callback with active index
  - Text input detection: Prevents arrow key handling when typing in inputs
  - Boundary wrapping: Arrow right from last column wraps to 0; arrow left from 0 wraps to last

**Keyboard Handling Logic**:
- Calculates current row and column from `activeIndex`
- Down arrow: Moves to next row in same column; wraps to first row if at bottom
- Up arrow: Moves to previous row in same column; wraps to last row if at top
- Auto-scroll: Uses `scrollIntoView({ block: 'nearest' })` to keep active item visible

**Special Behaviors**:
- Validates `activeIndex` against `itemCount` (adjusts if out of bounds)
- Ignores keyboard input when modifier keys (meta/ctrl/alt) are pressed
- Disables arrow key handling when focus is on text inputs

---

### 2. GRID CONTEXT (`src/components/grid/grid_context.tsx`)

```typescript
interface GridContextValue {
  activeIndex: number;
  setActiveIndex: (index: number) => void;
  columns: number;
}
```

Provides read-only state to `GridItem` children for styling and mouse interaction.

---

### 3. GRID ITEM (`src/components/grid/grid_item/grid_item.tsx`)

**Props**:
```typescript
interface GridItemProps {
  index: number;
  icon?: ReactNode;
  title: string;
  subtitle?: string;
  onClick?: () => void;
}
```

**Features**:
- Uses `GridContext` to determine if it's active
- On `mouseEnter`: Sets itself as active via `setActiveIndex(index)`
- Renders: Icon + Title + Optional Subtitle
- ARIA attributes: `role="option"`, `aria-selected={isActive}`

---

### 4. GRID STYLES (`src/components/grid/grid.scss`)

```scss
.grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(var(--grid-columns, 4), 1fr);
  gap: $space-2;           // 8px
  flex: 1;
  overflow-y: auto;
  padding: $space-2;       // 8px
}
```

---

### 5. GRID ITEM STYLES (`src/components/grid/grid_item/grid_item.scss`)

```scss
.grid-item {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  gap: $space-2;           // 8px
  padding: $space-3;       // 12px
  border-radius: $radius-md; // 8px
  cursor: pointer;
  border: 2px solid transparent;
  transition: transform 80ms, border-color 80ms, background-color 80ms;

  &:hover {
    background-color: $color-surface-hover; // #2a2a2d
    transform: scale(1.05);
  }

  &--active {
    border-color: $color-accent;     // #007aff (blue)
    background-color: $color-surface-hover;
  }
}

.grid-item__color-swatch {
  width: $size-grid-icon;    // 64px
  height: $size-grid-icon;   // 64px
  border-radius: $radius-lg; // 12px
}
```

---

### 6. SEARCH DROPDOWN (`src/components/search_bar/search_dropdown.tsx`)

**Type Definitions**:
```typescript
export interface SearchDropdownOption {
  label: string;
  value: string;
  icon?: ReactNode;
}

export interface SearchDropdownSection {
  title?: string;
  options: SearchDropdownOption[];
}

interface SearchDropdownProps {
  sections: SearchDropdownSection[];
  value: string;
  onChange: (value: string) => void;
  placeholder?: string; // Default: 'All'
}
```

**Core Functionality**:
1. **State Management**:
   - `open`: Boolean for dropdown visibility
   - `activeIndex`: Index of hovered/focused option in flat options array
   - `triggerRef` / `dropdownRef`: DOM references for focus management and click-outside detection

2. **Data Processing**:
   - `nonEmptySections`: Filters out empty sections
   - `flatOptions`: Merges all options from sections into single array
   - `sectionOffsets`: Tracks where each section's options start in the flat array

3. **Keyboard Navigation** (when open):
   - **ArrowDown**: Cycle forward through options; wrap to start
   - **ArrowUp**: Cycle backward through options; wrap to end
   - **Enter**: Select current option and close
   - **Escape/Tab**: Close dropdown and return focus to trigger

4. **Mouse Interaction**:
   - Click trigger button: Toggle open/closed
   - Click outside: Close dropdown
   - Mouse enter option: Set as active
   - Click option: Select and close

5. **Focus Management**:
   - Auto-focus dropdown when opened
   - Return focus to trigger button when closed
   - Scroll selected option into view on keyboard nav

6. **Visual States**:
   - Selected option: Shows checkmark icon
   - Active option: Highlighted with accent background
   - Sections: Support titles with separators

---

### 7. SEARCH DROPDOWN STYLES (`src/components/search_bar/search_dropdown.scss`)

```scss
.search-dropdown {
  position: relative;
  flex-shrink: 0;
}

.search-dropdown__trigger {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: $space-1;           // 4px
  padding: $space-1 $space-2; // 4px 8px
